article.headline: Colorado State 77, IUPUI 65
article.story: FORT COLLINS, Colo. (AP) -- Sean Morris scored 15 points on 6-for-6 free throw shooting as Colorado State matched its best start in 35 years with a 77-65 victory over IUPUI on Saturday. Jason Smith added 13 points and nine rebounds for Colorado State (6-0). The Rams shot 57 percent for the game and were 20-for-23 from the free throw line in starting the season with six wins for the first time since 1970-71. Brandon Cole led IUPUI (3-3) with 26 points on six 3-pointers. Matt Burks had three 3-pointers and 12 points for the Jaguars, who were 11-for-23 from beyond the arc. Cole got IUPUI within striking distance in the second half. His second 3-pointer of the period got the Jaguars to within 58-50 with 12:05 left. Michael Morris got the lead back to double digits with a jumper and Sean Morris maintained it with a 3-pointer with 10:07 left and then two free throws to make it 67-55. Sean Morris' 3-pointer was the last field goal of the game for Colorado State. The Rams were 14-for-14 from the free throw line over the final 9:27 of the game. IUPUI started the game hitting 6-of-11 3-pointers, three by Cole, to stay within 26-22. The Jaguars didn't hit another 3-pointer over the final 7:37 and with Colorado State heating up, 7-for-12, the Rams went on a 20-9 run to lead 46-31 at the half.
